description.narrative: Data and analytical evidence on child wellbeing, multidimensional poverty and vulnerability, disaggregated by sex, geographical areas and disability status, are regularly available to inform policy and monitor progress towards the child-relevant Sustainable Development Goals., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Building Capacity For Evaluation, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Economic And Social Policy General, Evaluation, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Reducing Child Poverty, Research, Social Exclusion â€“ Data And Evidence, Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, child poverty and well-being are regularly monitored, and social policies, especially social protection systems, are strengthened to favour the social inclusion of vulnerable girls and boys at the national and decentralized levels.

description.narrative: UNICEF Morocco has succeeded to convince the High Commission for Planning (HCP) to conduct a third round of the "COVID impact survey", with a sample of more than 10,000 households. Furthermore, in collaboration with National Human Development Observatory (ONDH) UNICEF Morocco, produce timely & relevant evidence as well as specific data on the socio-economic impact of COVID-19 on children, via modelling studies on child monetary, multidimensional poverty, and dissemination of the results of the international survey on Changing Childhood and impact of Covid on youth. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
